"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdevops_blog=self.webpackChunkdevops_blog||[]).push([["9834"],{2904(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"terraform-module-patterns","metadata":{"permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/terraform-module-patterns","editUrl":"https://github.com/souravgke052-coder/devops-blog/tree/main/blog/2025-06-05-terraform-module-patterns.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2025-06-05-terraform-module-patterns.mdx","title":"Terraform Module Patterns for Production","description":"Reusable module design patterns used in real-world infrastructure with Terraform and Google Cloud.","date":"2025-06-05T14:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"Terraform","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/terraform","description":"Infrastructure as Code with Terraform"},{"inline":false,"label":"IaC","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/iac","description":"Infrastructure as Code"},{"inline":false,"label":"GCP","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/gcp","description":"Google Cloud Platform tutorials and tips"},{"inline":false,"label":"Modules","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/modules","description":"Modular code and reusable components"},{"inline":false,"label":"Best Practices","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/best-practices","description":"Industry best practices and patterns"}],"readingTime":0.81,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"SouravLobra","title":"DevOps Engineer","url":"https://github.com/souravlobra","page":{"permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/authors/sourav"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/souravlobra","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/souravlobra/"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/souravlobra.png","key":"sourav"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"terraform-module-patterns","title":"Terraform Module Patterns for Production","description":"Reusable module design patterns used in real-world infrastructure with Terraform and Google Cloud.","date":"2025-06-05T14:00:00.000Z","authors":["sourav"],"tags":["terraform","iac","gcp","modules","best-practices"],"hide_table_of_contents":false},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"How I Passed the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer Exam","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips"}},"content":"After managing infrastructure across multiple projects, I\u2019ve distilled some **Terraform module patterns** that keep code clean, reusable, and maintainable.\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## The Layout Pattern\\n\\n```\\nmodules/\\n  gce_instance/\\n    main.tf\\n    variables.tf\\n    outputs.tf\\n  vpc/\\n    main.tf\\n    variables.tf\\n    outputs.tf\\n```\\n\\nEach module:\\n- Has a **single responsibility**\\n- Exposes only **intentional inputs** via `variables.tf`\\n- Returns **predictable outputs** via `outputs.tf`\\n\\n## Version Pinning\\n\\nAlways pin provider and module versions in production.\\n\\n```hcl\\nterraform {\\n  required_providers {\\n    google = {\\n      source  = \\"hashicorp/google\\"\\n      version = \\"~> 5.0\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Using `for_each` Over `count`\\n\\nUse `for_each` for named resources to avoid reordering issues.\\n\\n```hcl\\nvariable \\"subnets\\" {\\n  type = map(object({\\n    cidr = string\\n    region = string\\n  }))\\n}\\n\\nresource \\"google_compute_subnetwork\\" \\"default\\" {\\n  for_each = var.subnets\\n\\n  name          = each.key\\n  ip_cidr_range = each.value.cidr\\n  region        = each.value.region\\n  network       = google_compute_network.vpc.id\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Remote State with GCS\\n\\nStore state remotely to enable team collaboration.\\n\\n```hcl\\nterraform {\\n  backend \\"gcs\\" {\\n    bucket = \\"my-tf-state-bucket\\"\\n    prefix = \\"prod/infrastructure\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n- Use modules for reusable components\\n- Pin provider versions\\n- Prefer maps and `for_each` over lists and `count`\\n- Always use remote state in production\\n\\nWhat patterns do you use? Let me know in the comments!"},{"id":"gcp-associate-exam-tips","metadata":{"permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips","editUrl":"https://github.com/souravgke052-coder/devops-blog/tree/main/blog/2025-06-01-gcp-associate-exam-tips.mdx","source":"@site/blog/2025-06-01-gcp-associate-exam-tips.mdx","title":"How I Passed the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer Exam","description":"Study tips, resources, and hands-on strategies for passing the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer certification.","date":"2025-06-01T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"GCP","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/gcp","description":"Google Cloud Platform tutorials and tips"},{"inline":false,"label":"Certification","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/certification","description":"Study guides and exam tips"},{"inline":false,"label":"Cloud","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/cloud","description":"Cloud computing and platforms"},{"inline":false,"label":"Tips","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/tags/tips","description":"Quick tips and tricks"}],"readingTime":1.05,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"SouravLobra","title":"DevOps Engineer","url":"https://github.com/souravlobra","page":{"permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/authors/sourav"},"socials":{"github":"https://github.com/souravlobra","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/souravlobra/"},"imageURL":"https://github.com/souravlobra.png","key":"sourav"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"gcp-associate-exam-tips","title":"How I Passed the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer Exam","description":"Study tips, resources, and hands-on strategies for passing the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer certification.","date":"2025-06-01T10:00:00.000Z","authors":["sourav"],"tags":["gcp","certification","cloud","tips"],"hide_table_of_contents":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Terraform Module Patterns for Production","permalink":"/devops-blog/blog/terraform-module-patterns"}},"content":"Passing the **Google Cloud Associate Cloud Engineer** exam requires a mix of hands-on practice and focused study. Here are the strategies that worked for me.\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Study Resources\\n\\n- **Official Google Cloud documentation** \u2014 read it like a textbook\\n- **Google Cloud Skills Boost** \u2014 Quest: \\"Prepare for Your Associate Cloud Engineer Journey\\"\\n- **Practice exams** \u2014 Linux Academy / A Cloud Guru / Coursera\\n\\n## Key Focus Areas\\n\\n1. **IAM & Identity**\\n   - Understand the difference between primitive, predefined, and custom roles\\n   - Know when to use Service Accounts vs User Accounts\\n\\n2. **Compute Engines**\\n   - Know how to create and manage GCE instances\\n   - Understand startup scripts and metadata\\n\\n3. **Kubernetes Engine (GKE)**\\n   - Deploy clusters using Console and `gcloud`\\n   - Know basic `kubectl` commands\\n\\n4. **Storage & Databases**\\n   - Cloud Storage bucket classes and use cases\\n   - When to use Cloud SQL vs Cloud Spanner vs BigQuery\\n\\n## Hands-On Practice\\n\\nCreate a mini project: deploy a VM, attach a persistent disk, configure a firewall rule, and host a simple app.\\n\\n```bash\\ngcloud compute instances create web-server \\\\\\n  --image-family=debian-11 \\\\\\n  --image-project=debian-cloud \\\\\\n  --machine-type=e2-micro \\\\\\n  --zone=us-central1-a \\\\\\n  --tags=http-server\\n```\\n\\n## Exam Day Tips\\n\\n- Flag uncertain questions and return later\\n- Know the pricing model basics (sustained use discounts, committed use)\\n- Time management: 2 hours for 50 questions\\n\\nGood luck!"}]}}')}}]);